<subSubSection id="28FB6564FFD2D65C0DA6F53C1B0A3B0D" pageId="4" pageNumber="695" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="605E36EFFFD2D65C0DA6F53C18703D0D" blockId="4.[2028,2622,2768,3191]" pageId="4" pageNumber="695">
<emphasis id="5295EAFDFFD2D65C0DA6F53C19A73CF4" bold="true" box="[2028,2184,2768,2797]" pageId="4" pageNumber="695">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFD2D65C02EFF53C191E3D0D" authority="Waterhouse, 1845" authorityName="Waterhouse" authorityYear="1845" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="695" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tristis">Vespertilio tristis Waterhouse, 1845</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="D0893CB2FFD2D65C0208F51718703D0D" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3747914303" box="[2114,2399,2811,2836]" pageId="4" pageNumber="695">
“ 
<collectingCountry id="18F6767FFFD2D65C0207F51718603D0D" box="[2125,2383,2811,2836]" name="Philippines" pageId="4" pageNumber="695">Philippine Islands</collectingCountry>
.”
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="605E36EFFFD2D65C0DA6F4F71B0A3B0D" blockId="4.[2028,2622,2768,3191]" lastBlockId="4.[1414,2621,3197,3466]" pageId="4" pageNumber="695">
The name #ristis was used for a long time for all large species of 
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFD2D65C0302F4AE18CC3D7A" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1837" box="[2376,2531,2882,2915]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="695" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Miniopterus</taxonomicName>
living from the 
<collectingCountry id="18F6767FFFD2D65C023AF48518213D93" box="[2160,2318,2921,2954]" name="Philippines" pageId="4" pageNumber="695">Philippines</collectingCountry>
to Melanesia. Several studies, including very complete multivariable morphometric analyses, showed that it was actually a new species complex, with 1-2 species (
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFD2D65C02EAF3EB19C83A31" authorityName="Waterhouse" authorityYear="1845" box="[2208,2279,3079,3112]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="695" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="tristis">tristis</taxonomicName>
and propatristis) and five subspecies. There is some genetic information that supports existence of at least two species. Based on current data, it is impossible to assign the different subspecies to one or the other species and therefore, a single species with five subspecies is maintained, awaiting detailed genetic study to clarify taxonomy. There are some misclassified records that are actually 
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFD2D65C0D6BF31F16E63B0D" authorityName="Sanborn" authorityYear="1931" box="[1825,1993,3315,3348]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="696" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="magnater">M. magnater</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="A7E14D6CFFD2D65C0244F31F19B73B0D" authorityName="Bonaparte" authorityYear="1837" baseAuthorityName="Temminck" baseAuthorityYear="1840" box="[2062,2200,3315,3348]" class="Mammalia" family="Miniopteridae" genus="Miniopterus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="698" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="blepotis">M. blepotis</taxonomicName>
. Five subspecies recognized.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
